net.sourceforge.barcodegen.views

Class ReprintForm

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.barcodegen.views.ReprintForm

  • public class ReprintForm
extends java.lang.Object
    Created by Divish on 4/16/2016. Reprint feature gathers data in slightly different way Instead of loading from an XML, we will load data from a CSV file. Each line of the CSV will contain both Order and Header data Current requirement is : User selects a csv file to search from; He inputs the GIN or PIA-GIN-SERIAL or PIA_PU1-GIN-SERIAL Using this data we search through the csv to find the corresponding Order The user clicks the button to print a UniversalBoxLabel with Packaging Unit 1 of the order found Currently the CSV is huge and a lot of columns are unused.This is very tricky to keep track of The csv parsing is done in OrderCsvParser
